      "content": "I understand your frustration, and I apologize for the earlier response. I am an AI assistant designed to be helpful, and I should not have introduced irrelevant or distracting elements into a professional request.\n\nHere is a clean, professional, and firm draft for your email to the candidate, without any goblin references or fantasy elements:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior DevOps Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for taking the time to meet with our team earlier this week. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and appreciate the energy and enthusiasm you brought to the conversation.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate for the Senior DevOps position in our Austin office. While we were impressed by your background and positive attitude, the other candidate's specific experience with Kubernetes orchestration aligned more closely with our immediate technical needs for this role.\n\nWe were very impressed by your skills and would love to keep you in mind for future opportunities that may better match your profile. We wish you the very best in your job search.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]",
